article.headline: Georgia State 70, Alabama State 59
article.story: ATLANTA (AP) -- Leonard Mendez scored 17 points and Lance Perique added 15, leading Georgia State past Alabama State 70-59 Tuesday night. The Panthers (2-2) began pulling away for their second straight win with a 9-1 spurt to start the second half, increasing the lead to 41-28 with 17 1/2 minutes remaining. Georgia State was up by as many as 22 points before it cleared the bench late in the game. Moses Edun scored 15 points to lead Alabama State (0-2), while Deshean Porchea chipped in with 10. In a matchup of brothers, Georgia State freshman Kevin Lott scored four points, grabbed seven rebounds and blocked a shot, while Alabama State junior Richard Lott scored six points, blocked a shot of his own and was the game's top rebounder with 12. Their parents watched from the stands at the GSU Sports Arena. Georgia State dominated the boards with a 48-32 rebounding edge and continually got inside to draw fouls. The Panthers went 27-of-36 at the free-throw line.
